overview: "The user initiated a request to fix a pull request with numerous
  issues, including critical security vulnerabilities and functional bugs,
  alongside persistent Vercel deployment failures. The agent systematically
  addressed each problem: first, resolving lint errors and implementing a secure
  HMAC-based session management system using Web Crypto API for Edge Runtime
  compatibility. Pagination and input validation were enhanced for API routes
  and CSV exports. PDF generation was improved to handle empty time inputs and
  include minute calculations, and form fields were updated to support null
  values. The 'Download PDF' button was wired up, and a hardcoded user name was
  replaced. A significant portion of the effort focused on debugging Vercel
  deployment issues, which involved adding and then removing the
  from the Prisma schema due to a Next.js update that pulled in Prisma 7. This
  also necessitated updating Next.js to version 16.1.1 to fix a critical CVE,
  which in turn required a complete overhaul of the ESLint configuration due to
  breaking changes. Finally, the Prisma client was lazy-loaded to prevent
  build-time connection errors on Vercel. Despite all code fixes, the Vercel
  deploys continued to fail, indicating a need for the user to configure
  essential environment variables (, ,
  ) directly in the Vercel dashboard."
